@startuml
' Filename: Female_Horizontal_Control_State_Diagram.plantuml
' Diagram Type: State Diagram
' Authored 2026-07-18 from the live engine: src/simulation/behavior/state-machine-female.ts
' (bodyStopRequest = phase != "satisfaction-search") + src/simulation/oscillator-step.ts
' (stepOscillator hold/release). The Female horizontal control oscillator (her "body")
' HOLDS at the reinforcement position during satisfied-and-indifferent and engaging-partner,
' and only RELEASES to search (sweep) during satisfaction-search.

[*] --> Hold

state "Hold - stopped at reinforcementPosition" as Hold {
  ' bodyStopRequest = true  ->  requestMode "hold"  (lane act_stop_request_body)
  ' active during satisfied-and-indifferent, engaging-partner, and satisfaction display
  [*] --> MoveToReinforcementGoal
  MoveToReinforcementGoal --> AtReinforcementGoal : |pos - reinforcementPosition| <= tolerance
  MoveToReinforcementGoal --> MoveToReinforcementGoal : trapezoidal step toward reinforcementPosition
  AtReinforcementGoal --> MoveToReinforcementGoal : held at reinforcementPosition every tick
}

state "Release - oscillating (searching)" as Release {
  ' bodyStopRequest = false  ->  requestMode "release"  (search tier)
  ' active ONLY during satisfaction-search; sweeps motionProfile.min <-> max
  [*] --> SeedLeg
  SeedLeg --> MoveToGoal : first leg from mid-span heads toward max
  MoveToGoal --> MoveToGoal : not yet at goal (accelerate / cruise / decelerate)
  MoveToGoal --> FlipDirection : |pos - goal| <= tolerance
  FlipDirection --> MoveToGoal : goal = opposite stop (min <-> max)
}

Hold --> Release : phase -> satisfaction-search
Release --> Hold : phase -> engaging-partner\nor satisfied-and-indifferent\nor satisfaction animation

legend right
  Sources: src/simulation/behavior/state-machine-female.ts, src/simulation/oscillator-step.ts.
  The engine emits one bit (bodyStopRequest, lane act_stop_request_body); the harness maps
  it onto the child oscillator's requestMode at the agent boundary (stop -> "hold").
  reinforcementPosition is a fixed scene-config value (typically 0 deg / center).
endlegend

@enduml
